TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {7084=Terry had previously been demoted from the role in the run-up to the 2010 World Cup following lurid tabloid stories about his private life which led to Wayne Bridge's retirement from international football., 10075=Bernstein on Thursday contacted all the other members of the 12-strong board to seek their views after the decision that the defender's trial will not take place until July 9 - after Euro 2012. Terry has been accused of racially abusing QPR's Anton Ferdinand, a charge he denies., 13057=Fri, 03 Feb 11:57:00 2012, 9735=English football's governing body took the decision to act immediately rather than putting off a decision until the next board meeting on February 23., 8354="The FA board can confirm that he has not been excluded from the squad and that Fabio Capello is free to select him for the Holland fixture on 29 February and the European Championship., 9569=The FA released a statement around an hour after the news broke on Friday which reads: "Following the decision to adjourn the court case against John Terry to July, the Football Association confirm he will not captain the England team until the allegations against him are resolved.}
